  "title": "Giving Gifts: Likes and Dislikes (Levantine)",
  "dialect": "levantine",
  "steps": [
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Expressing 'I like' and 'I don't like'",
          "arabic": "التعبير عن 'أنا أحب' و 'أنا لا أحب'"
        },
        "text": "To express what you like or don't like in Levantine Arabic, you use the verbs 'بحب' (b7ibb) for 'I like' and 'ما بحب' (ma b7ibb) for 'I don't like'. These are commonly used when discussing preferences, including gifts.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "أنا بحب الورد.",
            "english": "I like flowers.",
            "transliteration": "Ana b7ibb il-ward."
          },
          {
            "arabic": "أنا ما بحب الشوكولاتة.",
            "english": "I don't like chocolate.",
            "transliteration": "Ana ma b7ibb ish-shokolata."
          }
        ],
        "audioText": "أنا بحب الورد. أنا ما بحب الشوكولاتة."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Key Vocabulary: Gift",
          "arabic": "مفردات أساسية: هدية"
        },
        "text": "The word for 'gift' in Levantine Arabic is 'هدية' (hadiyye). To say 'to give a gift', you can use 'أعطي هدية' (a3Te hadiyye) or 'قدم هدية' (2addam hadiyye).",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "هاي هدية حلوة.",
            "english": "This is a nice gift.",
            "transliteration": "Hay hadiyye 7elwe."
          },
          {
            "arabic": "بدي أعطيه هدية.",
            "english": "I want to give him a gift.",
            "transliteration": "Biddi a3Teh hadiyye."
          }
        ],
        "audioText": "هاي هدية حلوة. بدي أعطيه هدية."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Common Gift Items",
          "arabic": "هدايا شائعة"
        },
        "text": "Let's learn some common gift items. Knowing these will help you express what you like or suggest for others.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "ورد",
            "english": "Flowers",
            "transliteration": "Ward"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "كتاب",
            "english": "Book",
            "transliteration": "Ktaab"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "شوكولاتة",
            "english": "Chocolate",
            "transliteration": "Shokolata"
          }
        ],
        "audioText": "ورد، كتاب، شوكولاتة."
      }
    },
