    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Asking 'What do you like?'",
          "arabic": "كيف تسأل 'ماذا تحب؟'"
        },
        "text": "To ask someone what they like, you'll use 'شو' (shu) for 'what' and conjugate the verb 'تحب' (t7ibb) according to gender. Remember: 'بتحب' for male and 'بتحبي' for female.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "شو بتحب؟",
            "english": "What do you (m) like?",
            "transliteration": "Shu bte7ebb?"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "شو بتحبي؟",
            "english": "What do you (f) like?",
            "transliteration": "Shu bte7ebbī?"
          }
        ],
        "audioText": "شو بتحب؟ شو بتحبي؟"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "More Gift Categories",
          "arabic": "المزيد من فئات الهدايا"
        },
        "text": "Let's expand our vocabulary for gift categories. These are common choices for gifts.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "لباس / تياب",
            "english": "Clothes",
            "transliteration": "Lbaas / tyaab"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "عطر",
            "english": "Perfume",
            "transliteration": "3eTer"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "إلكترونيات",
            "english": "Electronics",
            "transliteration": "Elektroniyyaat"
          }
        ],
        "audioText": "لباس، تياب، عطر، إلكترونيات."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Expressing 'I prefer'",
          "arabic": "التعبير عن 'أنا أفضّل'"
        },
        "text": "When you want to express a stronger preference or choose between options, you use 'بفضّل' (bfaDDel) which means 'I prefer'.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "أنا بفضّل العطر ع اللباس.",
            "english": "I prefer perfume over clothes.",
            "transliteration": "Ana bfaDDel il-3eTer 3a l-lbaas."
          },
          {
            "arabic": "هي بتفضّل الكتب.",
            "english": "She prefers books.",
            "transliteration": "Hiyye btefaDDel il-kutub."
          }
        ],
        "audioText": "أنا بفضّل العطر ع اللباس. هي بتفضّل الكتب."
      }
    },
