    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Expressing Gratitude: 'Thank you'",
          "arabic": "التعبير عن الشكر: 'شكراً'"
        },
        "text": "When receiving a gift, it's essential to express gratitude. The most common way to say 'thank you' is 'شكراً' (shukran).",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "شكراً على الهدية.",
            "english": "Thank you for the gift.",
            "transliteration": "Shukran 3ala l-hadiyye."
          },
          {
            "arabic": "شكراً كتير!",
            "english": "Thank you very much!",
            "transliteration": "Shukran ktiir!"
          }
        ],
        "audioText": "شكراً على الهدية. شكراً كتير!"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Polite Response: 'You're welcome'",
          "arabic": "الرد المهذب: 'أهلاً وسهلاً'"
        },
        "text": "After someone thanks you for a gift, you can reply with 'أهلاً وسهلاً' (ahlan w sahlan) or 'عفواً' (3afwan) to mean 'you're welcome'.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "شكراً!",
            "english": "Thank you!",
            "transliteration": "Shukran!"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "أهلاً وسهلاً.",
            "english": "You're welcome.",
            "transliteration": "Ahlan w sahlan."
          }
        ],
        "audioText": "شكراً! أهلاً وسهلاً."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Praising a Gift: 'I love it!' / 'It's beautiful!'",
          "arabic": "مدح الهدية: 'أحببتها!' / 'إنها جميلة!'"
        },
        "text": "To show genuine appreciation for a gift, you can use phrases like 'حبيتها كتير!' (7abbaytha ktiir!) meaning 'I loved it a lot!' or 'حلوة كتير!' (7elwe ktiir!) meaning 'It's very beautiful!'",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "الهدية حلوة كتير، حبيتها!",
            "english": "The gift is very beautiful, I loved it!",
            "transliteration": "Il-hadiyye 7elwe ktiir, 7abbaytha!"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "يا الله، شو حلوة!",
            "english": "Oh my God, how beautiful!",
            "transliteration": "Ya Allah, shu 7elwe!"
          }
        ],
        "audioText": "الهدية حلوة كتير، حبيتها! يا الله، شو حلوة!"
      }
    },
