    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Politely Declining a Preference: 'Not my style/preference'",
          "arabic": "رفض تفضيل بلباقة: 'ليس أسلوبي/ذوقي'"
        },
        "text": "Sometimes a gift might not be exactly what you'd choose. To politely express this without being rude, you can say 'مو ستايلي' (muu stayli) meaning 'not my style' or 'مو ذوقي' (muu zaw2i) meaning 'not my taste/preference'.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "هاي الهدية مو ستايلي.",
            "english": "This gift is not my style.",
            "transliteration": "Hay il-hadiyye muu stayli."
          },
          {
            "arabic": "معليش، بس مو ذوقي.",
            "english": "Excuse me, but it's not my taste.",
            "transliteration": "Ma3leesh, bas muu zaw2i."
          }
        ],
        "audioText": "هاي الهدية مو ستايلي. معليش، بس مو ذوقي."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Gift Occasions: Birthday and Anniversary",
          "arabic": "مناسبات الهدايا: عيد الميلاد وعيد الزواج"
        },
        "text": "Gifts are often given for special occasions. Two common ones are 'عيد ميلاد' (3iid miilaad - birthday) and 'عيد زواج' (3iid zawaaj - wedding anniversary).",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "رح أجيب هدية لعيد ميلاده.",
            "english": "I will get a gift for his birthday.",
            "transliteration": "Ra7 ajiib hadiyye la-3iid miilado."
          },
          {
            "arabic": "مبروك عيد زواجكم!",
            "english": "Congratulations on your wedding anniversary!",
            "transliteration": "Mabruuk 3iid zawaajkom!"
          }
        ],
        "audioText": "رح أجيب هدية لعيد ميلاده. مبروك عيد زواجكم!"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Types of Gifts: Practical vs. Personalized",
          "arabic": "أنواع الهدايا: عملية مقابل شخصية"
        },
        "text": "People have different preferences regarding the nature of gifts. Some prefer practical gifts, others prefer personalized ones. 'هدايا عملية' (hadaya 3amaliyye) are practical gifts, and 'هدايا شخصية' (hadaya shakhsiyye) are personalized gifts.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "أنا بحب الهدايا العملية.",
            "english": "I like practical gifts.",
            "transliteration": "Ana b7ibb il-hadaya l-3amaliyye."
          },
          {
            "arabic": "هي بتفضّل الهدايا الشخصية.",
            "english": "She prefers personalized gifts.",
            "transliteration": "Hiyye btefaDDel il-hadaya sh-shakhsiyye."
          }
        ],
        "audioText": "أنا بحب الهدايا العملية. هي بتفضّل الهدايا الشخصية."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "practice-sentence",
